Rusty out of jail
with their big letters,

12:06.426 --> 12:07.861
and their numbers,
and their evidence,

12:07.895 --> 12:09.062
and their expert witnesses,

12:09.096 --> 12:10.530
and their knowledge
of the law,

12:10.563 --> 12:12.900
and their common sense,
and their reasoning ability.

12:12.933 --> 12:14.301
No, no, no, no.

12:14.334 --> 12:17.570
We gonna get Rusty out of jail
the Cuyler way.

12:19.272 --> 12:22.142
What exactly
is the Cuyler way?

12:22.175 --> 12:25.112
The Cuyler way is I got
a truck bed full of gasoline,

12:25.145 --> 12:27.414
and I'm gonna crash into
the outer wall of the prison.

12:27.447 --> 12:28.916
Then, I'm gonna slit
that guard's throat

12:28.949 --> 12:30.383
with this here buck knife.

12:30.417 --> 12:32.152
And I'm gonna split
the other guard's trachea

12:32.185 --> 12:34.788
with my Chinese ninja
throwin' stars.

12:34.822 --> 12:37.424
I don't think we should
do the Cuyler way.

12:37.457 --> 12:39.259
We should probably
look at people

12:39.292 --> 12:41.261
more successful
than the Cuylers

12:41.294 --> 12:43.163
and try doin' it
their way.

12:43.196 --> 12:45.765
I only know the Cuyler way,
damn it.

12:45.799 --> 12:48.368
Go! Wait, we're doin' this?

12:51.638 --> 12:53.473
I fell
on my damn knife!

12:53.506 --> 12:54.842
Where my throwin' stars?

12:54.875 --> 12:56.009
I can't see nothin'!
[ Groans ]

12:56.043 --> 12:57.344
By the way,
where is the prison?

12:57.377 --> 12:58.278
Are we inside?

12:58.311 --> 13:00.613
Oh, that ain't
the prison.

13:00.647 --> 13:02.615
That's the Waffle Barn.

13:02.649 --> 13:04.117
[ Explosion ]

13:04.151 --> 13:07.354
Oh, no!
I love me some waffles!

13:07.387 --> 13:08.755
Oh, no.

13:08.788 --> 13:09.923
What?
Aah!

13:09.957 --> 13:11.624
[ Clock chimes ]

13:11.658 --> 13:14.828
Are you sure you don't want
to pray to Jesus with me, Rusty?

13:14.862 --> 13:16.129
Why?

13:16.163 --> 13:17.364
My whole life,
Jesus' been crappin' on me.

13:17.397 --> 13:20.100
He made me poor, stupid,
gave me zits.

13:20.133 --> 13:22.035
Hell, I got back zits
on the back of my head

13:22.069 --> 13:23.636
'cause he didn't even
give me no back.

13:23.670 --> 13:26.639
My life's been a shit show.
Why would I want an encore?

13:26.673 --> 13:29.609
Aw, hold on, now.
Rusty, it ain't all that bad.

13:29.642 --> 13:33.180
You're about to get a pretty
slammin' last meal,

13:33.213 --> 13:35.382
courtesy of
the state of Georgia.

13:35.415 --> 13:36.984
Naw, I ain't hungry.

13:37.017 --> 13:38.185
Are you sure?

13:38.218 --> 13:39.987
Now, you get
whatever you want, Rusty.

13:40.020 --> 13:41.989
It's your last meal.
A'ight.

13:42.022 --> 13:44.657
I-I want a cheeseburger
and a pizza.

13:44.691 --> 13:46.459
And a root beer float,
I guess.

13:46.493 --> 13:47.460
Okay.

13:47.494 --> 13:48.962
That gonna cover it?

13:48.996 --> 13:50.964
Um, I also want
a candy bar,

13:50.998 --> 13:52.832
deep fried like
they do at the fair.

13:52.866 --> 13:54.067
'Cause I ain't never
been to a fair.

13:54.101 --> 13:55.302
And I want eight churros

13:55.335 --> 13:57.037
so I can put a churro
on each finger

13:57.070 --> 13:58.671
and pretend like
I'm Churro Man.

13:58.705 --> 14:00.207
No problem,
Churro Man.

14:00.240 --> 14:02.976
We may have to push the
execution back a few hours,

14:03.010 --> 14:04.511
go out out, and round
all this stuff up,

14:04.544 --> 14:07.314
but I'm sure that'd be
all right with you, won't it?

14:07.347 --> 14:08.415
Oh, okay.

14:08.448 --> 14:11.351
Well, in that case, uh,
let me get 20 hot wings.

14:11.384 --> 14:13.386
Okay.
Dodo-bird hot wings.

14:13.420 --> 14:15.588
Wait,
aren't dodo birds extinct?

14:15.622 --> 14:17.991
Well, then you best "Jurassic
Park" them sons-of-bitches,

14:18.025 --> 14:19.092
'cause that's what I want.

14:19.126 --> 14:20.527
And I also got a hankering

14:20.560 --> 14:22.362
for an eight-piece
California roll.

14:22.395 --> 14:24.998
California's
3,000 miles from here.

14:25.032 --> 14:27.234
And I want 1,300 BLTs.

14:27.267 --> 14:29.336
Also, I don't like mayo.
So hold the mayo.

14:29.369 --> 14:31.104
But they come with mayo,
Rusty.

14:31.138 --> 14:33.240
We'd have to scrape
it all off by hand.

14:33.273 --> 14:34.874
Could I throw
in some onion rings?

14:34.908 --> 14:36.543
Yeah, one extra-large
onion rings

14:36.576 --> 14:38.711
for the preacher man.
God bless you, bro.

14:38.745 --> 14:39.879
Ah, all right.

14:39.913 --> 14:41.181
I gotta make some calls.

14:41.214 --> 14:42.615
Yeah, that's right you will.
Get on it!

14:42.649 --> 14:45.052
Or I'll do you
just like I done Boyd.

14:45.085 --> 14:46.219
So, you did kill Boyd?

14:46.253 --> 14:47.687
You know what?
H-H-Hold up.

14:47.720 --> 14:48.788
Cancel them onion rings.

14:48.821 --> 14:51.191
Come on, bro.
I prayed for you.

14:51.224 --> 14:53.260
You best pray for some
onion rings now, God man.

14:53.293 --> 14:55.262
'Cause you ain't gonna
get 'em in here.

14:57.064 --> 14:59.532
It just seems to me
the Cuyler way don't

14:59.566 --> 15:00.934
normally work out right.

15:00.968 --> 15:02.769
The Cuyler way
is the only way.

15:02.802 --> 15:05.238
Put your mask on
and keep your mouth shut.

15:05.272 --> 15:08.241
I'm runnin' this show.

15:08.275 --> 15:09.542
Denny: Can I help you?

15:09.576 --> 15:11.911
Uh, yeah, uh,
I'm President Jimmy Carter

15:11.945 --> 15:14.247
as you can see
from my face,

15:14.281 --> 15:15.448
and, uh,
I'm officially pardoning

15:15.482 --> 15:17.650
Rusty Cuyler,
so you best let him go.

15:17.684 --> 15:19.552
I hate to say this,
but I don't see you

15:19.586 --> 15:21.955
on the visitors list,
Mr. President.

15:21.989 --> 15:24.257
Is President Wolfman
on the list?

15:24.291 --> 15:25.993
Ah-rooo!
I done a-told you.

15:26.026 --> 15:27.627
You
Vice President Wolfman.

15:27.660 --> 15:28.428
Hey, Denny.

15:28.461 --> 15:29.929
Hey, Granny.
God damn it.

15:29.963 --> 15:31.931
Happy Halloween!
Put your mask back on.

15:31.965 --> 15:34.067
You'll compromise
the whole operation.

15:34.101 --> 15:38.171
♪ Amazing Grace

15:38.205 --> 15:42.175
♪ How sweet the sound

15:42.209 --> 15:44.277
This is Doug Richards
reporting live outside

15:44.311 --> 15:47.280
Dougal County Maximum
Security Correctional Facility,

15:47.314 --> 15:49.482
where convicted murderer
Russell Cuyler

15:49.516 --> 15:52.085
awaits execution
by lethal injection

15:52.119 --> 15:53.353
in less than an hour.

15:53.386 --> 15:55.322
Sheriff: H-How you gonna eat
all these BLTs

15:55.355 --> 15:57.457
before 8:00, Rusty?
[ Chuckles ]

15:57.490 --> 15:59.859
I guess your eyes
were bigger than your stomach,

15:59.892 --> 16:02.762
wasn't they?
Did you hear my joke?

16:02.795 --> 16:06.466
I can't see ya, so I-I don't
know if you're smiling or not.

16:06.499 --> 16:08.468
Uh, hey, you think
maybe I could, uh,

16:08.501 --> 16:09.669
have half
of one of these?

16:09.702 --> 16:11.871
Rusty: Hell, no!
I want all 1,300.

16:11.904 --> 16:12.872
All right, I'm sorry!

16:12.905 --> 16:14.207
I-I'll put it back.

16:14.241 --> 16:15.608
That's right,
you will.

16:15.642 --> 16:17.510
I'm about to fill my mouth
with some food, now,

16:17.544 --> 16:19.179
and I don't like to talk
with my mouth full.

16:19.212 --> 16:20.480
So I'm gonna be chewin',

16:20.513 --> 16:21.981
and I ain't gonna talk
for a long time.

16:22.015 --> 16:24.884
Well, Rusty, don't eat too
fast and choke and die,

16:24.917 --> 16:28.621
'cause that's gonna mess up us
havin' to kill ya, you know?

16:28.655 --> 16:29.822
[ Laughs ]

16:29.856 --> 16:33.360
Did you hear that joke?
I still can't see ya.

16:33.393 --> 16:36.163
[ Clears throat ] You know,
I bet he's smiling in there.

16:36.196 --> 16:37.964
Did you hear my joke,
Thomas?

16:37.997 --> 16:39.499
[ Laughs ]

16:39.532 --> 16:41.000
♪♪

16:41.034 --> 16:42.802
[ Grunting ]

16:42.835 --> 16:47.574
♪♪

16:47.607 --> 16:49.809
Man: Mmm. Yeah.

16:49.842 --> 16:57.050
♪♪

16:57.084 --> 16:58.418
[ Toilet flushes ]

16:58.451 --> 17:03.723
♪♪

17:03.756 --> 17:06.526
[ Pinging ]

17:06.559 --> 17:09.696
♪♪

17:09.729 --> 17:10.863
[ Retches ]

17:10.897 --> 17:15.202
♪♪

17:15.235 --> 17:17.537
[ Clicking, air blowing ]

17:17.570 --> 17:20.440
♪♪

17:20.473 --> 17:22.008
Aaaaahhh!

17:22.041 --> 17:23.176
Ow.

17:23.210 --> 17:24.544
[ Dryer buzzes ]

17:24.577 --> 17:26.279
♪♪

17:26.313 --> 17:27.714
Muchas gracias, Jesus.

17:27.747 --> 17:29.582
Good thing I didn't
shank you, right?

17:31.884 --> 17:35.622
No, it doesn't. Life is random
and we all die alone.

17:35.655 --> 17:37.457
But I love you anyway,
brother.

17:37.490 --> 17:42.562
♪♪

17:42.595 --> 17:44.397
Good luck
with the racial purity, Ricky.

17:44.431 --> 17:46.433
You'll get there.
White power, Rusty.

17:46.466 --> 17:48.101
Leroy,
death to whitey, right?

17:48.135 --> 17:49.269
Damn straight.

17:49.302 --> 17:50.403
You ready to do this,
Ricky?

17:50.437 --> 17:51.871
Ready as I'll ever be.

17:51.904 --> 17:53.240
[ Grunting ]

17:53.273 --> 17:54.741
-Fight!
-There's a fight!

17:54.774 --> 17:57.144
[ Alarm blaring ]

17:57.177 --> 17:59.312
♪♪

18:03.350 --> 18:06.419
[ Screaming ]

18:10.457 --> 18:11.758
Waaa!

18:11.791 --> 18:18.631
♪♪

18:18.665 --> 18:25.272
♪♪

18:25.305 --> 18:32.145
♪♪

18:32.179 --> 18:36.583
♪ Was blind but now...

18:36.616 --> 18:38.818
[ Gasping ] I'm free,
mother-[bleep]

18:38.851 --> 18:40.019
Daddy!
Rusty!

18:40.052 --> 18:41.354
Ugh.
What are you doin'?

18:41.388 --> 18:43.690
Oh, I just busted my green
ass out of prison --

18:43.723 --> 18:45.625
the Cuyler way.
Ba-bam!

18:45.658 --> 18:47.660
We've just gotten word
from the governor's office

18:47.694 --> 18:51.030
that Russell Cuyler is
receiving a stay of execution

18:51.063 --> 18:53.333
until his case can be reviewed
by the State Supreme Court.

18:53.366 --> 18:54.367
[ Cheering ]
Yes!

18:54.401 --> 18:55.635
Rusty, did you hear that?

18:55.668 --> 18:57.770
The governor's gonna
review your case!

18:57.804 --> 19:00.840
You mean I gotta go back in
there and wait for due process?

19:00.873 --> 19:03.643
Dagummit.

19:03.676 --> 19:05.144
Oh, God.

19:05.178 --> 19:08.348
Rusty's been torn
to bits by rats.

19:08.381 --> 19:10.149
He deserves better.

19:10.183 --> 19:11.484
Oh, no, Sheriff.
It's okay.

19:11.518 --> 19:12.552
I'm here.
I'm alive.

19:12.585 --> 19:14.787
Oh!
Oh, thank God.

19:14.821 --> 19:17.957
I thought that lettuce
was you, Rusty.

19:17.990 --> 19:19.292
Did you hear
the good news?

19:19.326 --> 19:21.328
You're probably gonna get
out of here soon.

19:21.361 --> 19:24.397
Turns out, I didn't have
any evidence on you at all.

19:24.431 --> 19:26.165
It's all right, Sheriff.
I get it.

19:26.199 --> 19:27.500
White privilege.

19:27.534 --> 19:28.835
You saw an opportunity
to sell a minority

19:28.868 --> 19:30.503
up the river
and you pounced on it.

19:30.537 --> 19:32.405
I sure did.
But, look,

19:32.439 --> 19:35.074
I didn't ask to be born white,
so in some ways,

19:35.107 --> 19:37.176
I-I guess
we're both victims.

19:37.210 --> 19:38.478
Are we cool here, now?

19:38.511 --> 19:40.413
Sure, Sheriff.
Blow it up, Rusty.

19:40.447 --> 19:41.481
Stick this! Shove it! No!

19:41.514 --> 19:43.416
Die, pig!
Oh, mommy!

19:43.450 --> 19:44.584
Ohh!
It's all right, Sheriff.

19:44.617 --> 19:46.419
You alive.
Collapsible.

19:46.453 --> 19:48.355
I made it in shop
out of a radio antenna.

19:48.388 --> 19:50.323
Oh, thank God.

19:50.357 --> 19:52.992
Whew!
I nearly wet myself.

19:53.025 --> 19:55.362
Well, that's a strange
definition of "nearly."

19:55.395 --> 19:58.831
♪♪

19:58.865 --> 20:00.267
♪ The food was pretty good

20:00.300 --> 20:02.369
♪ And I got my GED

20:02.402 --> 20:04.036
♪ I asked for 1,300 BLTs

20:04.070 --> 20:06.406
♪ And they gave it to me!

20:06.439 --> 20:09.509
♪ Mayo-free, man!

20:09.542 --> 20:10.877
♪ Even though I got framed

20:10.910 --> 20:12.545
♪ I ain't afraid

20:12.579 --> 20:16.449
♪ The Po-po tried to put me
back in the cage ♪

20:16.483 --> 20:19.919
♪ I'm ready, bitches

20:19.952 --> 20:22.755
♪ God willing,
with help from above! ♪

20:22.789 --> 20:26.726
♪ This ain't the last jail time
for this dirty dove! ♪

20:26.759 --> 20:29.796
♪♪

20:29.829 --> 20:32.031
Oh, that was a good song,
honey.

20:32.064 --> 20:34.567
Yeah. I know. I texted
them lyrics to Steve Earle,

20:34.601 --> 20:36.769
and he just texted back "K."

20:36.803 --> 20:39.306
So, then I asked him when he
was playing Dougal county again

20:39.339 --> 20:41.207
and maybe I could
sing it at the show,

20:41.240 --> 20:42.542
and he ain't got back to me.

20:42.575 --> 20:44.544
Rusty, none of them
fancy-pants lawyers

20:44.577 --> 20:47.447
that got you off
or them high-stepping bands

20:47.480 --> 20:50.082
that raised all that money
for your legal defense

20:50.116 --> 20:51.651
are gonna be
your real friends.

20:51.684 --> 20:53.886
The only real, true friends
you're gonna have

20:53.920 --> 20:55.955
are right here
in Dougal cou--

20:55.988 --> 20:57.089
[Bleep] you, law dog!

20:57.123 --> 20:59.459
You tried to have me killed
by lethal injection!

20:59.492 --> 21:00.893
He 'bout mad as hell.

21:00.927 --> 21:02.094
He gon' kill again.

21:02.128 --> 21:03.630
Easy now, killer!
Whoo-hoo!

21:03.663 --> 21:06.333
Did they ever find out
who iced Boyd?

21:06.366 --> 21:09.336
Funny story --
turns out Boyd had leukemia,

21:09.369 --> 21:11.671
he didn't
have health insurance either,

21:11.704 --> 21:14.006
so his wife shot him.
[ Laughs ]

21:14.040 --> 21:17.243
A-And I guess his wife
blamed it on you

21:17.276 --> 21:19.912
so she could collect
life insurance.

21:19.946 --> 21:22.449
She thought no one would
call it into question

21:22.482 --> 21:24.584
because you're poor
and uneducated,

21:24.617 --> 21:26.319
and, frankly [Chuckles]

21:26.353 --> 21:29.456
we're incompetent.
[ Laughs ]

21:29.489 --> 21:31.424
That story ain't funny.

21:31.458 --> 21:33.793
No, it is not.

21:33.826 --> 21:37.364
♪ Hey,
ain't supposed to be here ♪

21:37.397 --> 21:39.799
♪♪

21:39.832 --> 21:43.436
♪ Hey,
ain't supposed to be here ♪

21:43.470 --> 21:45.805
♪♪

21:45.838 --> 21:49.809
♪ Hey,
ain't supposed to be here ♪

21:49.842 --> 21:51.678
♪♪

21:51.711 --> 21:55.147
♪ Rustlin' like a dove
in an iron cage ♪

21:55.181 --> 21:57.450
♪♪

